                        Edgar
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d397</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">397</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-05-21T02:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-05-21T02:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-21T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-21T02:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5–2149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-21T16:00:00+09:00">May 21, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 22—6:41 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>181. Persistent rumor in Taiwan that top level Kmt conference in preparation
                    there. Local officials vacating residences for exalted guests. K. C. Wu<note n="33" xml:id="d397fn33">Former Mayor of Shanghai.</note> and Tao
                        Hsi-sheng<note n="34" xml:id="d397fn34">Chinese Vice Minister of the
                        Kuomintang Ministry of Information.</note> there now. Generalissimo
                    expected. Constant rumors Generalissimo already in Taiwan but best information
                    says still Yangtze anchorage although quarters at Sun-Moon Lake and Taipei have
                    been prepared.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 181, repeated Canton 42, Shanghai 145.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
